						               													<description>Trivia game based on a brazilian magazine.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has 6000 questions (500 for children) about news published on past editions of the magazine Veja in six categories: economy and businness, general knowledge, world, arts and entertainment, sports, Brazil.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The gameplay is very simple: each player receives a pawn and a booklet of questions. Each turn the current player must throw two six-sided dice: a numerical one (10, 20, 30) and a colored one. The player on the left must open the booklet and ask a question of a certain type (10, true or false; 20, multiple choice; 30, direct question) about the category indicated by the colored dice. For instance, if the result of the dice are 20 and green, the player on the left must ask a multiple choice question about Brazil. If the current players gives the correct answer he must move his pawn 2 green spaces ahead. If the answer is incorrect the pawn is moved one space back. In the last part of the board the players must answer questions about all subjects and move their pawns only one space ahead for each correct answer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the one of the players reachs the final space on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
